        "subject": "LU-951 tests: wait import state in fail()",
        "message": "LU-951 tests: wait import state in fail()\n\nThere still has a rare chance that the request meets\nan invalid import after fail() returns. So we should wait\nimport restored to a certain state before doing the next\noperation.\n\nThe fail() function can only be used in the situation\nthat before failing a server target, all of the Lustre\nclients have $MOUNT mounted as Lustre filesystem.\n\nFor the case that not all of the Lustre clients are mounted\non $MOUNT before failing a server target, we need use\nfail_nodf() to fail the server target, and then run\nwait_clients_import_state() and client_up() to check the\npreviously live clients.\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=SLOW=yes,ENABLE_QUOTA=yes \\\ntestlist=replay-dual,replay-vbr,recovery-small\n\nSigned-off-by: Jian Yu <jian.yu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iaa6a42595e22b2959f78dc884569dd4ac137a2b8\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
